# The openwrt/luci commit this project takes its two BORROWED BUILD TOOLS from, and their
# checksums. Sourced as shell (`. luci-upstream.pin`) by update-po.sh and by the CI workflow.
#
# Both tools are downloaded over the network and then EXECUTED as gates:
#   - jsmin.c        is compiled and decides whether our shipped JavaScript is safe
#                    (jsmin's regex-vs-division lookback can silently eat a file — see CLAUDE.md)
#   - i18n-scan.pl   is run by perl and decides whether the translation catalogue is complete
# Fetching either from a moving `master` would mean the gate is whatever upstream pushed last.
#
# THIS FILE IS THE SINGLE SOURCE OF THE COMMIT. It used to be written out twice — once in
# .github/workflows/build.yml and once in update-po.sh — each with a comment saying "bump them
# together, deliberately", and nothing whatsoever holding them together. Bumping one and
# forgetting the other left half the toolchain on an older tree, silently.
#
# To bump: change LUCI_PIN, re-fetch both files at the new commit, and update their sha256s.
LUCI_PIN=5cf20c5741dc34eea0faaf7324ef3751b05fa1f3
JSMIN_SHA256=0568b14873f27f339cf66a9c43603d0bc8ca501ff62522ea924c6e8daf1be215
I18N_SCAN_SHA256=a1823d1fdd942f31a105e1e53b401e146bc10527f231e016930b1a5123ef21d3
